# General Guidelines
- Maintain a single-page scrolling layout similar to https://www.socratica.info/
- Ensure a smooth and seamless navigation experience between sections
- Keep the design minimal, clean, and professional
- Prioritize readability with appropriate font sizes, spacing, and contrast
- Ensure full responsiveness for desktop, tablet, and mobile views

# Code Structure
- Use modern HTML, TailwindCSS, and Typescript
- Organize sections in a clear, logical order: Header, Introduction, Current Highlights, About Us, Events, Participation, Our Team, Contact, Footer
- Keep CSS styles modular and avoid inline styles
- Use semantic HTML for better accessibility and SEO
- Implement lazy loading for images to optimize performance

# Navigation
- Implement a fixed top navigation bar with smooth scrolling between sections
- Use anchor links (e.g., `#about`, `#events`) for navigation
- Highlight the active section in the navbar based on scroll position

# Responsiveness
- Ensure mobile-first design, using media queries for larger screens
- Optimize touch interactions for mobile users
- Avoid horizontal scrolling; all content should fit within the viewport

# Performance
- Optimize images and assets for faster loading (WebP format preferred)
- Minimize and bundle CSS/JS files where possible
- Use caching strategies to improve load times

# Accessibility
- Ensure proper use of ARIA attributes where needed
- All text should have sufficient contrast against its background
- Make sure the website is navigable via keyboard (Tab, Enter, etc.)

# Footer
- Include links to social media, legal information, and a subscription/newsletter option
- Keep it minimal yet informative, avoiding unnecessary clutter

# Additional Considerations
- Maintain existing content while improving its presentation
- Use smooth scroll animations where appropriate but avoid excessive animations
- Ensure compatibility with all major browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
